# ---- Rust ----
# Compiled output
/target/
**/target/

# Backtrace / debug
*.pdb

# Cargo lock is kept for binaries/workspaces; uncomment if this is a library
# Cargo.lock

# rustc incremental / coverage
*.profraw
*.gcda
*.gcno

# proptest failure-persistence artifacts (auto-generated cache; not stable across runs)
**/*.proptest-regressions

# ---- Editor / OS ----
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# ---- OSS / Cloud split (per `00-vision-and-principles.md` §6) ----
# The OSS workspace (this directory) is the public open-source runtime.
# The cloud-heavy trait impls live in `kx-cloud/` and are PRIVATE — they will
# be developed in their own (separate, private) git repository nested inside
# this subdirectory when P5.5 begins. Until then, the directory holds only a
# stubbed Cargo workspace as an architectural breadcrumb. NEVER commit
# kx-cloud contents to the OSS repo.
kx-cloud/

# ---- Internal docs (kept out of the public OSS repo) ----
# These live in the working tree but never land in `Kortecx/kortecx`. Wildcards
# auto-cover future additions so a new design / suggestion doc doesn't leak by
# accident.
/00-*.md
/01-*.md
/02-*.md
/03-*.md
/04-*.md
/05-*.md
/06-*.md
/CLAUDE.md
/docs/design/*.md
/docs/suggestions/*.md
